Art. 5. Foreigners of any nation whatever, and natives of this re-
public,
can project the formation of new towns upon lands entirely va-
cant;
and, in the ease of article 35, even upon those privately appro-
priated;
but the new settlers, who present themselves to be admitted,
shall prove, by certificate from the authorities of the place from which
they came, their Christianity and good moral character.
